<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-195-298  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 195 298.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  March 1990 v7 n3 p107(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Putting the professor on disk. (Authorware Inc.'s AuthorwareProfessional)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Littman, Dan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Northern Telecom exec Richard Oliver used Authorware Professional,an application generation program, to recreate a lecture onpolitical risk analysis and market entry decision factors.andP;  The14Mbyte application was incorporated as part of the graduatecourse on international marketing Oliver teaches at VanderbiltUniversity.andP;  The two-hour computer course uses digitizedphotographs, text, color charts and a point-and-click world map toillustrate the development of global beer-export strategies.andP;  Theprogram concludes with a quiz.andP;  Authorware Professional enablesthe creation of graphics and animations and allows PICS-formatfiles and sounds to be imported.andP;  The $8,000 AuthorwareProfessional can only be purchased directly from Authorware.andO;Authorware Academic is available to the academic community for$495, but lacks color, animation and sound features.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Authorware Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Authorware Professional (Program development software) (usage).andO;Topic:     Program Development ToolsTeachingEducationProgram GeneratorsInstructional Design.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>